{"amendments":[{"body":"`src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:464-490` drops the caller-provided `started_at`, and `src/adapters/fs.rs:2982-3009` resolves runless completions only by `(bead_id, project_id)`. That breaks the supported `run_id = None` retry path when the same project is reused: after the second runless attempt is finalized, any replay of `record_bead_completion` for that attempt fails with `ambiguous task run update ... provide run_id to disambiguate`, so a partial snapshot/journal write can no longer be repaired. `started_at` needs to be used to pick the attempt, or the API needs to forbid same-project runless retries entirely.","rationale":"I reproduced this with two runless `project-1` attempts: the first completion succeeded, but replaying the second completion immediately afterward returned the ambiguity error even though the caller still had the original `started_at`."},{"body":"`src/adapters/fs.rs:2770-2845` allows starting the same bead again as long as the other active row is for the same `bead_id`; it only rejects a different active bead. `src/contexts/milestone_record/service.rs:163-204` then rebuilds snapshot state from `latest_task_runs_per_bead`, which keeps only the newest attempt per bead. The result is that if `bead-1/project-1/run-1` is still `Running`, `bead-1/project-2/run-2` can start, and once `run-2` reaches a terminal state the milestone snapshot moves to `ready` with `in_progress_beads = 0` even though `task-runs.ndjson` still contains the older running attempt. Start logic needs to reject or explicitly supersede any prior running attempt for the same bead, not only same-project legacy rows.","rationale":"I reproduced this by starting `run-1`, starting `run-2` for the same bead, and then failing `run-2`: the snapshot became `Ready` while the lineage file still had `run-1` marked `Running`."}],"summary":"Reviewed the milestone lineage/model/service/FS changes and ran `cargo test milestone_record -- --nocapture` successfully. I found two correctness gaps: completion replay is broken for valid runless same-project retries, and the start flow can leave snapshot state inconsistent with lineage by allowing multiple live attempts for the same bead."}